<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Requirements. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
In addition to other requirements that may be imposed by the applicable state statutes and regulations and other federal
statutes and regulations, including &sect;303.15 of this chapter, an insured mutual state savings bank shall not
convert to the stock form of ownership unless the following requirements are satisfied: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The subscription offering of the stock to be offered or sold in the conversion shall provide a stock purchase priority
to eligible depositors, other depositors and others entitled to vote on the bank's proposed conversion residing
in the bank's local community or within 100 miles of a home office or branch of the converting bank; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Employee stock ownership plans shall not have priority over subscription rights of eligible depositors; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Any direct community offering by the converting bank shall give a purchase priority to natural persons residing
in the bank's local community or within 100 miles of a home office or branch of the bank; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The proposed conversion shall be approved by a vote of at least a majority of the bank's depositors and other stakeholders
of the bank who the bank's trustees reasonably determine are entitled to vote on the conversion, unless the applicable
state law requires a higher percentage, in which case the higher percentage shall be used. Voting may be in person or
by proxy; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Management shall not use proxies executed outside the context of the proposed conversion to satisfy the voting
requirement imposed in paragraph (d)(4) of this section; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) In addition to the materials to be submitted to the FDIC pursuant to &sect;303.15(c) of this chapter, the bank must
submit to the FDIC: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A full appraisal report on the value of the converting bank and the pricing of the stock to be sold in the conversion.
The report must be prepared by an independent appraiser and must include a complete and detailed description of the
elements that make up an appraisal report, justification for the methodology employed and sufficient support for
the conclusions reached therein, including a full discussion of the applicability of each peer group member and documented
analytical evidence supporting any variance (above or below) the institution proposing to convert may have from
the peer group statistics and a complete analysis of the institution's 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
pro forma
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 earnings which should include its full potential once the institution fully deploys its new capital pursuant to its
business plan; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) A business plan which must include, in part, a detailed discussion of how the capital acquired in the conversion
will be utilized, expected returns resulting from the plan and a justification for any proposed stock repurchases.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Restriction on repurchase of stock.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 An insured mutual state savings bank that has converted from the mutual to stock form of ownership may not repurchase
its capital stock within one year following the date of its conversion to stock form. Any stock repurchases after the
one year period shall be subject to the requirements of section 18(i)(1) of the Federal Deposit Insurance Act (12 U.S.C.
1828(i)(1)). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Stock benefit plan limitations.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 No converted insured mutual state savings bank shall, for one year from the date of the conversion, implement a stock
option plan or management or employee stock benefit plan, other than a tax-qualified employee stock ownership plan,
unless each of the following requirements is met: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Each of the plans was fully disclosed in the proxy soliciting and conversion stock offering materials; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) All such plans are approved by a majority of the bank's stockholders, or in the case of a recently formed holding
company, its stockholders, prior to implementation and no sooner than the first annual meeting following the conversion;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) In the case of a savings bank subsidiary of a mutual holding company, all such plans are approved by a majority of
stockholders other than its parent mutual holding company prior to implementation and no sooner than the first annual
meeting following the stock issuance; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) For stock option plans, stock options are granted at no lower than the market price at which the stock is trading
at the time of grant; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) For management or employee stock benefit plans, no conversion stock is used to fund the plans. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

