<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart I_Lender Liability 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;280.200 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Definitions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
UST technical standards,
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 as used in this subpart, refers to the UST preventative and operating requirements under 40 CFR part 280, subparts
B, C, D, G, and &sect;280.50 of subpart E. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Petroleum production, refining, and marketing._
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Petroleum production
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the production of crude oil or other forms of petroleum (as defined in &sect;280.12) as well as the production
of petroleum products from purchased materials. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Petroleum refining
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the cracking, distillation, separation, conversion, upgrading, and finishing of refined petroleum or petroleum
products. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Petroleum marketing
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the distribution, transfer, or sale of petroleum or petroleum products for wholesale or retail purposes. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Indicia of ownership
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means evidence of a secured interest, evidence of an interest in a security interest, or evidence of an interest in
real or personal property securing a loan or other obligation, including any legal or equitable title to real or personal
property acquired incident to foreclosure or its equivalents. Evidence of such interests include, but are not limited
to, mortgages, deeds of trust, liens, surety bonds and guarantees of obligations, title held pursuant to a lease financing
transaction in which the lessor does not select initially the leased property (hereinafter ``lease financing transaction''),
legal or equitable title obtained pursuant to foreclosure, and their equivalents. Evidence of such interests also
includes assignments, pledges, or other rights to or other forms of encumbrance against property that are held primarily
to protect a security interest. A person is not required to hold title or a security interest in order to maintain indicia
of ownership. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
A holder
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 is a person who maintains indicia of ownership (as defined in &sect;280.200(c)) primarily to protect a security interest
(as defined in &sect;280.200(f)(1)) in a petroleum UST or UST system. A holder includes the initial holder (such as
a loan originator); any subsequent holder (such as a successor-in-interest or subsequent purchaser of the security
interest on the secondary market); a guarantor of an obligation, surety, or any other person who holds ownership indicia
primarily to protect a security interest; or a receiver or other person who acts on behalf or for the benefit of a holder.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
A borrower, debtor, or obligor
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 is a person whose UST or UST system is encumbered by a security interest. These terms may be used interchangeably. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Primarily to protect a security interest
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means that the holder's indicia of ownership are held primarily for the purpose of securing payment or performance
of an obligation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Security interest
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means an interest in a petroleum UST or UST system or in the facility or property on which the UST or UST system is located,
created, or established for the purpose of securing a loan or other obligation. Security interests include but are
not limited to mortgages, deeds of trusts, liens, and title pursuant to lease financing transactions. Security interests
may also arise from transactions such as sale and leasebacks, conditional sales, installment sales, trust receipt
transactions, certain assignments, factoring agreements, accounts receivable financing arrangements, and consignments,
if the transaction creates or establishes an interest in an UST or UST system or in the facility or property on which
the UST or UST system is located, for the purpose of securing a loan or other obligation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Primarily to protect a security interest,
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 as used in this subpart, does not include indicia of ownership held primarily for investment purposes, nor ownership
indicia held primarily for purposes other than as protection for a security interest. A holder may have other, secondary
reasons for maintaining indicia of ownership, but the primary reason why any ownership indicia are held must be as
protection for a security interest. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;280.210 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Participation in management. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The term 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
participating in the management of an UST or UST system
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means that the holder is engaging in acts of petroleum UST or UST system management, as defined herein. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Actions that are participation in management pre-foreclosure.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Participation in the management of an UST or UST system means, for purposes of this subpart, actual participation
in the management or control of decisionmaking related to the UST or UST system by the holder and does not include the
mere capacity or ability to influence or the unexercised right to control UST or UST system operations. A holder is
participating in management, while the borrower is still in possession of the UST or UST system encumbered by the security
interest, only if the holder either: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Exercises decisionmaking control over the borrower's environmental compliance, such that the holder has undertaken
responsibility for the borrower's UST or UST system management; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Exercises control at a level comparable to that of a manager of the borrower's enterprise, such that the holder
has assumed or manifested responsibility for the overall management of the enterprise encompassing the day-to-day
decisionmaking of the enterprise with respect to: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Environmental compliance; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) All, or substantially all, of the operational (as opposed to financial or administrative) aspects of the enterprise
other than environmental compliance. Operational aspects of the enterprise include functions such as that of facility
or plant manager, operations manager, chief operating officer, or chief executive officer. Financial or administrative
aspects include functions such as that of credit manager, accounts payable/receivable manager, personnel manager,
controller, chief financial officer, or similar functions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
